      <section eId="sec_CC-3344">
        <num>CC 3344</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-3344__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as otherwise provided by law, the recorder shall refuse to record:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CC-3344__subsec_A__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>An instrument that does not bear the original signature of a party.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CC-3344__subsec_A__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A judgment, administrative decree, or other act of a governmental agency that
is not properly certified in a manner provided by law.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3344__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Recordation does not dispense with the necessity of proving that the signatures
are genuine unless they are authenticated in the manner provided by law.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110393</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
